Season 5 - Episode 4 of A Cup of Gratitude is available tomorrow!!! (Link in bio) We are premiering the new song of Laurel Taylor!!! Her song “Old House” officially releases on January 27th, but you can hear it first on this Special Episode!! Laurel shared her incredible story on Season 4 - Episode 3 - and Her parents were so moved that they shared their story on Season 4 a Episode 10 - I have come to love Laurel and her family and believe so strongly in her heart and her amazing talent !!! This week we sit down for a second interview - You will hear behind the scenes of her new song, how and why it was written, what genre it’s crossing lines to play in, and the faith it takes to follow where God wherever He is leading!! And as a special treat we will play “Old House” for you - You won’t want to miss this incredible song! In case you haven’t been listens to our first interview,  Musical guest Laurel Taylor is a singer-songwriter and producer whose roots and influences of rock, country, and gospel blend together to give her a unique and edgy sound. She has toured worldwide, from small-town music festivals to the bars of Nashville to European tours. She has worked with and performed with various artists, including Lauren Daigle, Jason Crabb, Micah Tyler, Kutless, Sanctus Real, Rhett Walker, Diamond Rio, and CCR. She has a heart full of joy and a desire to share the love of Jesus with everyone through her music.

I have learned that....

/ not everyone is for you 
/ not everyone is against you 
/ not everyone will like you

The biggest struggle about being an artist is NOT the talent, style, or lack of sleep you get. It IS being confident in the Lord and yourself while discerning His voice out of all voices with opinions and concerns you receive daily. 

Sometimes it can be too much handle, but I hold on to the TRUTH. 
We all need clarity on a daily basis.

Welcome to week three of the Christmas Break Special Episodes! Available Now (link in Bio) - This week’s question is: Who is being fed by the harvest of your life? God wants to use you! Think about it: if you’re producing a great harvest and have a fruitful life for the kingdom, if you share the truths you have received from the gospel, can others take from what you produce and be fed? I write books, have a podcast, speak on stage, and share my harvest anywhere I can. When a seed produces a harvest in good soil, it isn’t just for the life where the harvest grows; even the very edges of what you produce can feed others - God’s ways amaze me! Today, I am challenging you to look for the places where you are leaving some room for people who are hurting and hungry to GLEAN - “And when you reap the harvest of your land, you shall not reap your field right up to its edge, nor shall you gather the gleanings after your harvest. You shall leave them for the poor and the sojourner, I am the LORD your God.” Leviticus 23:22. Who are the poor and the foreigners near you? Who are the sojourners around your life? This week, we have special music by Laurel Taylor, an artist, producer, and singer/songwriter in Nashville, Tennessee. Originally from Alabama, she moved to Music City twelve years ago, right after turning eighteen. Her voice and sound speak to every crowd, from the American Idol stage to Tootsies on Broadway to the local church leading worship. Laurel carries an excellent stage presence and live show performance everywhere she goes. She has a raw country sound, a ministry mindset, and her own unique style. Laurel uses her life stories to speak to people through her music and intentionally writes for everyone who listens. #reels #reelsinstagram #reelitfeelit #reelsvideo #reelsviral #christian #womanoffaith #shineyourlight #gleaning #listen #whereyougoiwillgo #whereyoustayillstay

What an amazing time we have had working our way towards Christmas together - I always love sharing these special episodes on A cup of Gratitude podcast (if you missed any go to the link in my bio and catch up!)- this last week we will see what Jesus’ name and title have to tell us about who came to save the world - I share with you things you have not heard before and the power and purpose of names in the Bible, how they tell an extremely important part of the story - We started on week one looking at how and when you were created with purpose, followed by week two where we inspected the soil of the heart and the necessary gardening we must do to have good soil, then last week we were challenged to consider who could be fed by the edges of our harvest fields - and finally in week four I will reveal some powerful truths about the deity and the mercy, of the great all encompassing love, of Jesus Christ - you won’t want to miss this final encouragement for Christmas - And as a bonus, this week I feature another beautiful song by @laureltaylorofficial ✨Tune in to “A Cup of Gratitude” for week four  Available on Christmas Day and consider the miracle of Jesus coming to Us all #reels #christmas #jesus #godsolovedtheworld #reelsinstagram #reelitfeelit #reelsvideo #reelsviral #christian #womanoffaith
